        <p class="section-number">01 — About This Service</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">In LA's apartment-dense market, a down commercial washer isn't just an inconvenience — it's a tenant complaint waiting to happen.</h2>

        <p>Los Angeles has the highest concentration of multi-unit rental buildings in the western US. Koreatown, Echo Park, Silver Lake, the Wilshire corridor, and dozens of other neighborhoods are dense with apartment buildings ranging from 8 units to 200+, most of which have shared laundry rooms with commercial washers. When a machine goes down, property managers get tenant complaints within hours — not days.</p>

        <p>For laundromat operators, the math is even more direct: a commercial washer running 15 cycles per day at $3.50–$6.00 per cycle generates $50–$90 per machine per day in coin or card revenue. A machine down for a week is $350–$630 in lost revenue — far more than the typical repair cost. We dispatch commercial washer calls same day because this calculation is real and the operators calling us know it.</p>

        <p>We service all major commercial washer brands with Speed Queen parts specifically stocked on service vehicles — Speed Queen is the dominant brand in LA's apartment laundry rooms and laundromats. For Continental Girbau, UniMac, Wascomat, and Electrolux Professional, we source parts through same-day commercial parts distributors.</p>
      </div>

