<!-- REVENUE MATH -->
<section class="section section-black">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">02 — The Revenue Math on a Down Machine</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Why same-day repair pays for itself — the numbers for LA laundromat and property operators</h2>

    <div class="revenue-block">
      <div class="r-label">💰 Lost Revenue Per Machine Per Day</div>
      <h3>A down commercial washer costs more in lost revenue than almost any repair</h3>
      <p>LA laundromat operators typically see 10–18 cycles per day per machine during normal operating hours. At current coin/card rates of $3.50–$6.00 per wash cycle in the LA market, that's $35–$108 per machine per day in gross revenue. A machine down for just 5 days represents $175–$540 in lost income — often exceeding the repair cost several times over.</p>
      <p>For apartment building property managers, the calculus is different but the urgency is similar. A down washer in a shared laundry room generates tenant complaints, potential requests for rent reduction for amenity failure, and negative reviews on platforms like Google and Yelp that affect vacancy rates. The cost of a same-day repair is minimal compared to these downstream effects.</p>

      <div class="r-grid">
        <div class="r-item"><strong>Laundromat — 15 cycles/day</strong><span>$3.50–$6.00/wash = $52–$90/day revenue per machine. 5-day downtime = $260–$450 lost</span></div>
        <div class="r-item"><strong>Apartment building</strong><span>Tenant complaints begin within hours. Risk: rent reduction requests, online reviews, vacancy impact</span></div>
        <div class="r-item"><strong>Hotel laundry</strong><span>Staff laundry capacity directly affects linen turnaround and guest room readiness</span></div>
        <div class="r-item"><strong>Gym / fitness center</strong><span>Towel service and member amenities directly tied to laundry equipment uptime</span></div>
        <div class="r-item"><strong>Typical repair cost</strong><span>$180–$500 for most commercial washer repairs — a fraction of the revenue loss from extended downtime</span></div>
        <div class="r-item"><strong>Multi-machine visits</strong><span>We service multiple machines on the same visit — maximizing uptime with one trip</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

