<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">08 — Frequently Asked Questions</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Commercial washer repair — what LA operators ask us</h2>

    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>How much does commercial washer repair cost in Los Angeles?</h3>
        <p>Commercial diagnostic is $120, applied to the repair if approved. Most repairs run $180–$500. Drain pump, motor coupling, door lock, door boot, or water inlet valve is in this range. Bearing replacement runs $300–$550. Written estimate before any work begins.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Do you repair coin-operated commercial washers?</h3>
        <p>Yes — the mechanical and electrical washer systems. Drain pump, motor, bearings, door lock, water inlet valve, control board. For coin acceptor and card reader electronics specifically, we assess on-site. The majority of coin-op failures are the washer, not the payment system — we'll tell you honestly which it is.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>My apartment building washer is not draining — can you come today?</h3>
        <p>Yes. We dispatch commercial washer calls same day. Call {phone} and describe the machine and symptom. For multi-machine laundry rooms, tell us how many machines are affected so we can bring the right parts.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Can you service multiple machines on the same visit?</h3>
        <p>Yes. For laundromats and multi-machine laundry rooms, we prioritize servicing all affected units on the same trip. Describe all machines needing service when you call — this lets us prepare for multiple repairs and minimize visits.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>How often should commercial washers be serviced?</h3>
        <p>Every 6 months for apartment building machines. Every 3–4 months for laundromat machines running 10–15 cycles per day. Regular maintenance catches drain pump wear, bearing degradation, and door boot deterioration before they become full failures.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Do you repair Speed Queen, Dexter, and Continental Girbau washers?</h3>
        <p>Yes. Speed Queen is the most common commercial washer in LA — we carry Speed Queen parts on the van. We also service Dexter, Maytag Commercial, Continental Girbau, UniMac, Wascomat, Electrolux Professional, and Huebsch.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Should I repair or replace my commercial washer?</h3>
        <p>Commercial washers last 10–15 years with proper maintenance. Under 8 years old, repair almost always makes sense — even a $400 repair on a machine generating $200+/week pays back in days. Over 12 years with motor or bearing failure, we'll give you an honest remaining-life assessment.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

